    <briefdescription>
<para>Deferred triviality evaluator for Pair&lt;T1, T2&gt;. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Placing the compiler intrinsics here, rather than directly in the <ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref>&lt;<ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt;&gt; enum, means they are only evaluated when this struct is explicitly instantiated. <ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref>&lt;<ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt;&gt; names <ref refid="structDali_1_1Detail_1_1PairIsTrivial" kindref="compound">PairIsTrivial</ref> in its enum initialiser but never instantiates it, so the intrinsics are not fired merely because <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt; appears in a type alias with incomplete T1 or T2.</para>
<para>The unused Dummy parameter prevents aggressive compilers (MSVC, GCC with -fno-implicit-templates) from pre-instantiating the value member when they see the ::value reference inside the <ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref> enum.</para>
<para>The intrinsics are applied directly to T1 and T2 (not to <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt; and not via <ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref>&lt;T1&gt;/TypeTraits&lt;T2&gt;) to avoid pulling in <ref refid="structDali_1_1BasicTypes" kindref="compound">BasicTypes</ref>, which would reintroduce the eager-evaluation problem.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T1</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>First element type of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T2</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Second element type of the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref> </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Dummy</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Unused; keeps the body dependent so it is not pre-instantiated </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
